-- STXNEWS LATAM-Banco de Chile shares drop as stake sale looms
-- By Antonio de la Jara
-- Fri Jan 10, 2014 07:49AM EST
-- None



Jan 10 (Reuters) - Shares of Banco de Chile <CHI.SN> fell in opening trade on Friday, the day after the Chilean bank's majority owner said it was seeking to sell the equivalent of up to around $1 billion in stock. [ID:nL2N0KJ2LX]

LQ Inversiones Financieras, owned by the wealthy Chilean Luksic family's Quinenco <QNN.SN> holding group and Citigroup Inc <C.N>, is seeking to divest up to 6.9 billion shares.